               <item n="m_remarks_old">&lt;p&gt;Although the fragments IOL Toch 579 (left, original size w: 3,9 cm, h: 4,4 cm) and IOL Toch 1187 (right, original size w: 3,6 cm, h: 4,4 cm) were edited separately in [[Peyrot 2008a]]: 100-102, they clearly belong together. There are no lines missing between a5 and b1, even though the lower margin of the recto (upper of the verso) is not itself preserved. The blank space to the left is probably not the string hole space (pace [[Peyrot 2008a]]: 100) because it seems to cover also line a5, which is the last; therefore, the left margin must be preserved. Still, the leaf number is not preserved: perhaps it stood left of lines b4-5.&lt;/p&gt;</item>
